ence Olivier]], and [[Maureen Stapleton]].\n\nMoore died of [[HIV/AIDS|AIDS-related]] pneumonia in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[AfterEllen.com and TheBacklot.com|AfterElton.com]]|date=2007|url=http://www.afterelton.com/movies/2007/6/gayfriendlydirectors|title=Gay Friendly Directors}}</ref>\n\n==Work==\n===Theatre===\n*''[[Promises, Promises (musical)|Promises, Promises]]'' (1968)\n*''[[The Last of the Red Hot Lovers]]'' (1969)\n*''[[The Gingerbread Lady]]'' (1970)\n*''[[Lorelei (musical)|Lorelei]]'' (1974)\n*''[[My Fat Friend]]'' (1974)\n*''[[Deathtrap (play)|Deathtrap]]'' (1978)\n*''[[They're Playing Our Song]]'' (1979)\n*''[[Woman of the Year (musical)|Woman of the Year]]'' (1981)\n\n===Filmography===\n====Film====\n*''[[Murder by Death]]'' (1976)\n*''[[The Cheap Detective]]'' (1978)\n*''[[Chapter Two (film)|Chapter Two]]'' (1979)\n\n====Television====\n* ''[[Diana (American TV series)|Diana]]'' (1973) \u2013 TV series\n*''[[Thursday's Game]]'' (1974) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''[[The Bob Newhart Show]]'' (1974) \u2013 TV series\n* ''[[Rhoda]]'' (1974\u20131975) \u2013 TV series\n* ''Don't Call Us'' (1976) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''[[Cat on a Hot Tin Roof#Adaptations|Cat on a Hot Tin Roof]]'' (1976) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''There's Always Room'' (1977) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''[[The Sunshine Boys#American versions|The Sunshine Boys]]'' (1977) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''The Natural Look'' (1977) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''Annie Flynn'' (1978) \u2013 TV movie\n* ''[[It's Not Easy]]'' (1983) \u2013 TV series\n\n====Actor====\n* ''[[Tell Me That You Love Me, Junie Moon]]'' (1970) \u2013 Warren\n* ''[[The Mary Tyler Moore Show]]'' (1973) \u2013 Ben Sutherland (1 episode)\n* ''[[Diana (American TV series)|Diana]]'' (1973) \u2013 Marshall Tyler (7 episodes)\n* ''[[Rhoda]]''  (1974\u20131976) \u2013 Lowell Snyder; Mr. Graham (2 episodes)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n;Awards\n* 1968 Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Direction of a Play \u2013 ''The Boys in the Band''\n;Nominations\n* 1969 T